* Trofeo 2º Carnaval del Fútbol de México 1971 – Copa Ciudad de México

Competition: Copa Ciudad de Mexico
Season: 1971

* Ciudad de México, Estadio Azteca

Round: Semifinals

8/10/1971; Atlante; 1-2;  East Germany; Estadio Azteca
José Luis Puente 87; Peter Ducke 31, Henning Frenzel 48

8/11/1971; Nacional de Montevideo; 1-1; América; Estadio Azteca
* (5-4 pen)

Round: Third Place

8/13/1971; Atlante; 3-2; América

Round: Final

8/13/1971; East Germany; 1-1; Nacional de Montevideo ; Arturo Yamasaki
* (6-6 pen)
East Germany: Jürgen Croy, Konrad Weise, Michael Strempel, Klaus Sammer, Bernd Bransch, Helmut Stein, Hans-Jürgen Dörner, Hans-Jürgen Kreische, Henning Frenzel, Peter Ducke, Eberhard Vogel.
Nacional de Montevideo: Aílton Corrêa de Arruda ‘Manga’; Juan Carlos Blanco, Atilio Ancheta, Juan Masnik, Juan Manuel Mujica; Ignacio Prieto, Julio Montero Castillo, Víctor Espárrago; Juan Carlos Mamelli, Luis Artime, Luis Alberto Cubilla
Notes: with the penalty shootout at 6-6, the East German goalkeeper Croy was accidentally injured by the Nacional goalkeeper Manga, and could not continue. The East German reserve goalkeeper was  ill, and so Nacional won the match (and tournament) by default.
